sources.description:
A young karate expert searches for her brother's killer in Hong Kong.

TNT Jackson, released also as Dynamite Wong and T.N.T. Jackson, is a 1974 American action, martial arts, blaxploitation film produced and directed by Cirio H. Santiago. The script was originally written by actor Dick Miller, but Roger Corman had it rewritten.

Members Only version: https://youtu.be/M4oha-kswXc


Main actors:
Jeanne Bell - Diana "TNT" Jackson
Chiquito - Joe "Dynamite" Wong
Stan Shaw - Charlie
Pat Anderson - Elaine
Ken Metcalfe - Sid
Imelda Ilanan - Joe's Assistant
Jose Mari Avellana - Ming (uncredited)
Joonee Gamboa - Dealer
Andres Centenera - Police Chief


@CultCinemaClassics

metadata.Plot: Her name is Diana Jackson, but you can call her T.N.T. When T.N.T.'s brother is killed by ruthless drug dealers, the beautiful young karate expert goes to the most dangerous part of Chinatown to find the killer. In trouble with the law since she was 13, T.N.T. wants no help from the pigs; but she does befriend a Chinaman named Joe, whose impressive martial arts skills prove useful more than once. In her quest for the killer, she'll meet the white drug lord, Sid; Elaine, his bitchy girlfriend; his suspicious Chinese assistant, Ming; and Charlie, his handsome black assistant with criminal ambitions of his own. Before her search is over, she'll find herself making love to Charlie, trading insults with Elaine, and fighting criminals while nude and in the dark. Just call her T.N.T.
metadata.Actors: Jeannie Bell, Stan Shaw, Pat Anderson
